arChildNodes.szComment:
INT. Feasting Hall.

THE PLAYER helps arrange items around Grelkar's body, including 4-5 candles. 
VARYANA pulls open Grelkar's shirt. (Don't need to show this part if this is not in scope)
Varyana draws a long, sharp knife.
The Player looks on, unsure...

Varyana wipes the back of her forearm across her mouth, as if wiping away sweat. It’s a sign that she is nervous, anxious. 
She drops to her knees next to the body, placing the tip of the dagger just below Grelkar’s sternum. 
She heaves a deep breath, and puts her weight into the knife, plunging it into the body. 
Her back to us, she begins carving open the body.

She puts her weight into the knife, PLUNGING it into the body.
We hear the wet sounds of meat being carved, and occasional grunts of effort from Varyana as she butchers the body. 
Varyana’s back remains to us, obscuring a good share of the graphic nature of what’s happening. 
But we can see blood pooling around the corpse, suggesting what a grim, grotesque process this is.

Varyana mutters low incantations, little more than whispers, as she goes about her work. 
The candles continue to burn. 
The Player takes a step forward.

Her back still to us, Varyana tears out an organ and tosses it over her shoulder. 
It lands with a wet splat just in front of the Player, arresting any forward motion. 
Varyana removes a kidney, then another, arranging them around the body. 
She pulls out intestines, arranging them in a pattern, still mostly obscured from our full vision. 

Varyana turns to glance over her shoulder at the Player.

The Player turns away from the grim spectacle. 
Varyana’s muttered incantation increases in volume, and we hear more cutting sounds. 
The candles flare brighter, casting the room in chiaroscuro shadows. 
The player can’t help but look toward her again. 
Her back still to us, Varyana pulls out the liver and holds it up. 
She turns her head toward the liver, so it’s barely inches from her mouth. 
The chanting is done, there's only silence. Varyana’s expression is a mixture of disgust and desire. Will she partake?   

 Cut to a close-up of Varyana’s hand/forearm, as rivulets of blood run down the arm. We hear sounds of wet chewing.

The chewing sounds continue as we cut to the Player for a reaction, one that is a mixture of distaste and something like grief. 
The Player realizes that Varyana has crossed a line she did not wish to cross.   

 Cut back to the standard view, Varyana now standing, her back to us. 
The bright candles suddenly blow out, smoke curling up from them. 
Varyana’s eyes roll back in her head and she sways unsteadily. 
She drops the liver with a wet plop. 
Varyana is overcome, in a trance state, speaking to herself haltingly as she narrates the vision she sees.

Varyana starts to collapse, but the player catches her before she hits the ground. 
Varyana’s eyes focus once again and she returns to normal. Or as normal as she gets. 
Varyana draws herself up to her full height again, ready to get back to business. 
She glances at the ruined corpse, not paying it a great deal of attention. 
Her gaze then settles on the half-eaten liver, and remains there for an uncomfortable moment, as if she’s contemplating what she’s done, if there’s a way back from crossing the line. 

She walks on, and the Player follows.
